{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bbea55d5-1cdb-408f-8f26-3dab7df66689","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them in the `.fsproj`. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GTLFbzhD3FOpJTM7KdrHOq","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-579981a8df284e2abf3e22fa9a8039aa/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-579981a8df284e2abf3e22fa9a8039aa/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"587e43ef-c0a1-46dd-8236-cff7706e55af","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them. Currently the order is:\n\n1. Services.fs (depends on Domain.fs)\n2. Domain.fs (defines types)\n3. Program.fs (depends on both)\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` needs to come first.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n\n\n2. Services.fs\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":452,"requestId":"F02C:161AD4:420DA93:49BF739:69F9B07C"},"id":"3df7904a-9e0d-4b10-8d2a-419f9fcf421c","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:55:31.885Z","parentId":"de21c465-59a3-4dd8-a19f-18d8f6412142"}
